# Cursor AI Clone - Project Rules

## Global Development Rules
- Always use TypeScript for new files
- Follow React functional component patterns with hooks
- Use Tailwind CSS for all styling
- Implement proper error handling with try/catch blocks
- Write comprehensive JSDoc comments for all functions
- Use async/await instead of .then() for promises

## Code Style Rules
- Use 2 spaces for indentation
- Prefer const over let when possible
- Use descriptive variable and function names
- Import React hooks at the top of components
- Group imports: external packages, internal modules, relative imports

## Electron Specific Rules
- Always use contextBridge for main-renderer communication
- Never expose Node.js APIs directly to renderer
- Use IPC for all file system operations
- Handle Electron app lifecycle events properly

## AI Integration Rules
- Always validate AI responses before processing
- Implement proper error handling for AI API calls
- Use streaming for real-time AI responses when possible
- Cache AI responses to improve performance
- Provide fallback behavior when AI is unavailable

## Security Rules
- Sanitize all user inputs
- Validate file paths before file operations
- Use Content Security Policy (CSP) headers
- Never execute arbitrary code from AI responses without validation

## Performance Rules
- Use React.memo for expensive components
- Implement lazy loading for heavy components
- Debounce AI requests to prevent spam
- Use virtual scrolling for large lists
- Optimize bundle size with code splitting

## Testing Rules
- Write unit tests for all utility functions
- Test React components with React Testing Library
- Mock external dependencies in tests
- Test error scenarios and edge cases
- Maintain test coverage above 80%

## Puter.js Integration Rules
- Always check if puter.js is available before use
- Implement fallback AI service when puter.js is unavailable
- Handle puter.js connection errors gracefully
- Use proper TypeScript types for puter.js responses
- Cache puter.js authentication if required